{"id":35,"parent_id":34,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":35,"title":"Mark 1: The Beginning of Jesus' Ministry","subtitle":"","short_title":"Mark 1: The Beginning of Jesus' Ministry","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-1-the-beginning-of-jesus-ministry","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-1-the-beginning-of-jesus-ministry"},[".heading",{"id":"head2","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-1-the-beginning-of-jesus-ministry.head2"},["h1","Mark 1"],[".subtitle","The Beginning of Jesus’ Ministry"],[".intro","While Matthew recorded many of the words Jesus spoke, Mark emphasized the events in the Savior’s life. Mark seems so anxious to write about Jesus’ ministry that he gives very little historical background, and in the first chapter he begins with what Jesus began doing among the people. Before you move too quickly to chapter 2, take time to ponder on what we learn about Jesus from the stories in chapter 1."]],[".bodyBlock",[".figure",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-1-the-beginning-of-jesus-ministry.f2"},["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["p.para"],[".",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-1-the-beginning-of-jesus-ministry.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-039-2a.gif"}]],["p"]],["td",["p.para"],[".",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-1-the-beginning-of-jesus-ministry.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-039-2b.gif"}]],["p"]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRe